We propose the following hypothesis: given that {{2111.13611_FO0128||FO}} is asserted to have high coverage, we can conclude that any statement not mentioned in {{2111.13611_FO0129||FO}} (like {{2111.13611_FO0130||FO}}) is more likely false. In contrast, the low coverage of {{2111.13611_FO0131||FO}} implies that {{2111.13611_FO0132||FO}} is unlikely to contain all factual statements. Thus, {{2111.13611_FO0133||FO}} not being found in {{2111.13611_FO0134||FO}} is no indication that it could not be true.